<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-05-26T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-05-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/5–2645: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the United States Representative in
                                Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-05-26T19:00:00-04:00">May 26,
                                    1945—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>148. You will of course not resist by force an attempt to take Dimitrov
                            by force but if he is removed from your house you should try with all
                            earnestness to obtain an assurance that he will be kept in safe custody
                            until the US, UK and Soviet Governments advise the Bulgarian authorities
                            of the positions which they individually or collectively wish to take in
                            the circumstances. Did you receive our 143 and 144 yesterday’s date and
                            today’s message to Moscow repeated to you?<note n="66" xml:id="d211fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                            </note> (Sent to Sofia, repeated to London, Moscow and Caserta.<note n="67" xml:id="d211fn2">As Nos. 4217, 1161, and 524,
                                respectively.</note>)</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>